  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Prenancy and specialy delivery for hemophilia mother and her children possibly hemophilia is
      risked.

      Diagnostical of hemophilia pregnan is the first difficulty but patients with hemorrhagic
      menstruation without etiology known, hemorrhagic complication during a chirurgical procedure
      or during previously pregnancy currently are examine in Haemostasis consultation.

      None French recommendation specifie for health practice of these hemophilia patients exists.
      However, Anglo-Saxon recommendations are published in 2011.

      The objective of this study is to realize a French investigation of health practice about
      hemophilia care of these patients and to compare them with the English reference table.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
